load ../delegated-wire-lifecycle.maude

--- Coverage: a terminal frame closes the run as an admitted lifecycle event.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-DELEGATED-WIRE-LIFECYCLE :
  running frameTerminal
  =>* terminal evtAdmitted .

--- Coverage: the clock backstop closes a silent run -- every live run reaches
--- a terminal.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-DELEGATED-WIRE-LIFECYCLE :
  running clockFired
  =>* terminal evtAdmitted .

--- Coverage: a misrouted frame is recorded as a violation while the run still
--- reaches its terminal -- tolerant routing does not abort the turn.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-DELEGATED-WIRE-LIFECYCLE :
  running frameMisrouted frameTerminal
  =>* terminal evtAdmitted violation .

--- Bite: exactly one terminal. Even with two terminal frames inbound, a state
--- with two `terminal` tokens is unreachable -- the second frame lands as a
--- violation diagnostic.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-DELEGATED-WIRE-LIFECYCLE :
  running frameTerminal frameTerminal
  =>* terminal terminal RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a cancel acknowledgement never completes the run.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-DELEGATED-WIRE-LIFECYCLE :
  running frameAck
  =>* terminal RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: post-terminal frames are never admitted as lifecycle events.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-DELEGATED-WIRE-LIFECYCLE :
  terminal frameStream
  =>* evtAdmitted RESIDUAL:Cfg .
